15 Georgia Fair Lending Act in 2003, which stood as the strongest anti-predatory lending
16 legislation in the nation at the time and protected consumers from abusive practices; and
17 WHEREAS, from 2011 to 2017, he served as the Minority Whip of the Georgia Senate
18 Democratic Caucus, during which time he championed legislation against discrimination,
19 racial profiling, environmental racism, and labor injustices while supporting fair wages, labor
20 unions, and stronger community protections; and
21 WHEREAS, the Honorable Vincent D. Fort was named "Legislator of the Year" in 2017 by
22 the Georgia Association of Educators for his advocacy of Senate Bill 30, which aimed to
23 improve public education funding and enhance community schools; and
24 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife, Cheryl, and the two were
25 blessed with three remarkable children, Nyahuma, Clara-Faith, and ZoÃ«, as well as three
26 wonderful grandchildren, Gizelle, Chloe, and Sunday; and
27 WHEREAS, the Honorable Vincent D. Fort was a powerful voice for economic and racial
28 equality, and his commitment to the people will leave a lasting impact on the City of Atlanta
29 and the State of Georgia.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
31 join in honoring the life and memory of the Honorable Vincent D. Fort and express their
32 deepest and most sincere regret at his passing.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
34 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the family of the
35 Honorable Vincent D. Fort.
